{"type":"message","id":"b2c9237b","parentId":"f7d22c9d","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:19:50.644Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01P3Ck5nsCRDuVvq1iVQe9BR","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_runtime.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01N4uBm9BMhnamHiLMTsjQMm","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\scene_director_runner.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":147,"cacheRead":14370,"cacheWrite":2387,"totalTokens":16905,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.002205,"cacheRead":0.004311,"cacheWrite":0.008951250000000001,"total":0.015470250000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775060382634,"responseId":"msg_011zYpVQMidTFohusxM8o9MV"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8bd52ff9","parentId":"b2c9237b","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:19:51.085Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01P3Ck5nsCRDuVvq1iVQe9BR","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"S1 Supervisor Runtime — canonical execution substrate for SM-S1.\n\nThis module is the execution substrate for the canonical S1 architecture.\nIt is intended to support the OpenClaw supervisor (`sm_s1_pre_production`) as the\nruntime brain of the sector.\n\nIt is NOT the legacy linear prototype path from `runtime.s1.s1_start`.\n\nDesign goal:\n- supervisor owns sequencing / acceptance / retry / completion decisions\n- deterministic skills and shared components perform mechanical work\n- OpenClaw operators perform semantic work\n- persisted artifacts remain operational truth\n\nInvocation strategy note:\n- canonical operator invocation should ultimately be performed through a real\n  OpenClaw runtime bridge\n- until a richer in-process bridge exists, this module may use an explicit\n  transitional adapter boundary for CLI/operator invocation\n- the adapter boundary is kept narrow on purpose so the architecture stays clear\n\nCurrent status:\n- scaffold / skeleton only\n- lane decomposition established\n- operator invocation hooks intentionally left explicit and narrow\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nimport shutil\nimport subprocess\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\nimport yaml\n\nfrom runtime.s1.checkpoint_writer import write_checkpoint\nfrom runtime.s1.polish_validator import validate_polish\nfrom runtime.s1.scene_bible_builder import build_scene_bible, write_scene_bible\nfrom runtime.s1.scene_bible_schema_validator import validate_scene_bible_schema\nfrom runtime.s1.screenplay_validator import validate_screenplay\nfrom runtime.s1.supervisor_skills.operator_batch_scheduler import (\n    build_batch_schedule,\n    summarize_batch_execution,\n)\nfrom runtime.s1.supervisor_skills.retry_planner import plan_retry\nfrom runtime.s1.supervisor_skills.s1_paths_resolver import resolve_paths\nfrom runtime.s1.supervisor_skills.s1_preflight_checker import run_preflight\nfrom runtime.s1.supervisor_skills.s1_result_summarizer import summarize_s1_result\nfrom runtime.s1.supervisor_skills.scene_director_io_adapter import write_scene_director_payload\nfrom runtime.s1.supervisor_skills.scene_director_output_validator import validate_scene_director_output\nfrom runtime.s1.supervisor_skills.screenplay_merger import merge_screenplay_batches\nfrom runtime.s1.supervisor_skills.script_batch_planner import plan_script_batches_from_file\nfrom runtime.s1.supervisor_skills.tts_polish_batch_planner import plan_tts_polish_batches\nfrom runtime.s1.supervisor_skills.tts_polish_io_adapter import write_tts_polish_payload\nfrom runtime.s1.supervisor_skills.tts_polish_merger import merge_tts_polish_batches\nfrom runtime.s1.supervisor_skills.tts_polish_output_validator import validate_tts_polish_output\n\n\nACCOUNTS_DIR = Path(__file__).parent.parent.parent / \"accounts\"\nDEFAULT_SCENE_DIRECTOR_CONCURRENCY = 2\nDEFAULT_TTS_POLISH_CONCURRENCY = 4\nDEFAULT_MAX_RETRIES = 3\n\n\ndef run_s1_supervisor_runtime(\n    *,\n    run_root: str | Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any] | None = None,\n    channel_config: dict[str, Any] | None = None,\n    model: str = \"gpt-4.1-mini\",\n    max_retries: int = DEFAULT_MAX_RETRIES,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Canonical execution substrate for S1 under supervisor authority.\n\n    This function intentionally decomposes the sector into lanes that map to the\n    canonical OpenClaw architecture.\n\n    Important:\n    - this module is the execution substrate, not the supervisor brain itself\n    - decision sovereignty still belongs to the supervisor layer\n    - operator invocation is left behind explicit hooks to avoid hiding architecture\n    \"\"\"\n    run_root = Path(run_root)\n    checkpoints_written: list[str] = []\n    all_warnings: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    all_errors: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n\n    preflight = run_preflight(run_root)\n    if not preflight.get(\"ok\"):\n        return _failed_result(run_root, preflight.get(\"errors\", []), preflight.get(\"warnings\", []))\n    all_warnings.extend(preflight.get(\"warnings\", []))\n\n    if job is None:\n        job = preflight.get(\"job\", {})\n\n    account = job.get(\"account\")\n    language = job.get(\"language\")\n    if channel_config is None:\n        channel_config = _load_config(account, language)\n\n    paths_result = resolve_paths(run_root, create_dirs=True)\n    paths = paths_result.get(\"paths\", {})\n    all_warnings.extend(paths_result.get(\"warnings\", []))\n\n    script_path = Path(preflight[\"paths\"][\"script_raw\"])\n    script_raw = script_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    screenplay_lane = _run_scene_director_lane(\n        run_root=run_root,\n        job=job,\n        channel_config=channel_config,\n        paths=paths,\n        script_path=script_path,\n        script_raw=script_raw,\n        model=model,\n        max_retries=max_retries,\n    )\n    all_warnings.extend(screenplay_lane.get(\"warnings\", []))\n    if not screenplay_lane.get(\"ok\"):\n        all_errors.extend(screenplay_lane.get(\"errors\", []))\n        return _failed_result(run_root, all_errors, all_warnings)\n\n    checkpoints_written.extend(screenplay_lane.get(\"checkpoints_written\", []))\n    screenplay = screenplay_lane[\"screenplay\"]\n    screenplay_result = screenplay_lane[\"screenplay_result\"]\n\n    polish_lane = _run_tts_polish_lane(\n        run_root=run_root,\n        job=job,\n        channel_config=channel_config,\n        paths=paths,\n        screenplay=screenplay,\n        model=model,\n        max_retries=max_retries,\n    )\n    all_warnings.extend(polish_lane.get(\"warnings\", []))\n    if not polish_lane.get(\"ok\"):\n        all_errors.extend(polish_lane.get(\"errors\", []))\n        return _failed_result(run_root, all_errors, all_warnings)\n\n    checkpoints_written.extend(polish_lane.get(\"checkpoints_written\", []))\n    polished = polish_lane[\"tts_polished\"]\n    polish_result = polish_lane[\"polish_result\"]\n\n    scene_bible_result = _run_scene_bible_lane(\n        run_root=run_root,\n        job=job,\n        screenplay=screenplay,\n        polished=polished,\n        paths=paths,\n    )\n    all_warnings.extend(scene_bible_result.get(\"warnings\", []))\n    if not scene_bible_result.get(\"ok\"):\n        all_errors.extend(scene_bible_result.get(\"errors\", []))\n        return _failed_result(run_root, all_errors, all_warnings)\n\n    checkpoints_written.extend(scene_bible_result.get(\"checkpoints_written\", []))\n\n    write_checkpoint(\n        run_root,\n        \"b1_complete\",\n        \"sm_s1_pre_production\",\n        [\n            \"b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\",\n            \"b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json\",\n            \"b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\",\n            \"b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json\",\n            \"scene_bible.json\",\n        ],\n        extra={\n            \"scene_count\": scene_bible_result.get(\"scene_count\", 0),\n            \"screenplay_validated\": True,\n            \"polish_validated\": True,\n            \"scene_bible_schema_valid\": True,\n        },\n    )\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_complete.json\")\n\n    return summarize_s1_result(\n        run_root=run_root,\n        screenplay_result=screenplay_result,\n        polish_result=polish_result,\n        scene_bible_path=scene_bible_result.get(\"scene_bible_path\"),\n        checkpoints_written=checkpoints_written,\n        warnings=all_warnings,\n        errors=all_errors,\n    )\n\n\ndef _run_scene_director_lane(\n    *,\n    run_root: Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    channel_config: dict[str, Any],\n    paths: dict[str, Any],\n    script_path: Path,\n    script_raw: str,\n    model: str,\n    max_retries: int,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    warnings: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    errors: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    checkpoints_written: list[str] = []\n\n    batch_plan = plan_script_batches_from_file(script_path)\n    warnings.extend(batch_plan.get(\"warnings\", []))\n    if not batch_plan.get(\"ok\"):\n        return _lane_fail(batch_plan.get(\"errors\", []), warnings)\n\n    prepared_batches = []\n    for batch in batch_plan.get(\"batches\", []):\n        batch_id = batch[\"batch_id\"]\n        input_path = Path(paths[\"scene_director_inputs_root\"]) / f\"{batch_id}_input.json\"\n        output_path = Path(paths[\"scene_director_intermediate_root\"]) / f\"{batch_id}_output.json\"\n        payload_result = write_scene_director_payload(\n            run_root=run_root,\n            job=job,\n            batch=batch,\n            channel_config=channel_config,\n            input_path=input_path,\n            output_path=output_path,\n        )\n        prepared_batches.append(\n            {\n                \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n                \"input_path\": payload_result[\"input_path\"],\n                \"output_path\": payload_result[\"output_path\"],\n                \"status\": \"queued\",\n            }\n        )\n\n    schedule = build_batch_schedule(\n        operator_name=\"scene_director\",\n        batches=prepared_batches,\n        concurrency_cap=DEFAULT_SCENE_DIRECTOR_CONCURRENCY,\n    )\n    if not schedule.get(\"ok\"):\n        return _lane_fail(schedule.get(\"errors\", []), warnings)\n\n    execution_results = []\n    for wave in schedule.get(\"waves\", []):\n        for batch in wave.get(\"batches\", []):\n            execution_results.append(\n                _invoke_scene_director_batch(\n                    input_path=batch[\"input_path\"],\n                    output_path=batch[\"output_path\"],\n                    model=model,\n                )\n            )\n\n    execution_summary = summarize_batch_execution(\n        operator_name=\"scene_director\",\n        concurrency_cap=DEFAULT_SCENE_DIRECTOR_CONCURRENCY,\n        execution_results=execution_results,\n    )\n    warnings.extend(execution_summary.get(\"warnings\", []))\n\n    approved_batch_files: list[str] = []\n    failed_batch_ids: list[str] = []\n    for batch in prepared_batches:\n        validation = validate_scene_director_output(\n            batch_payload_path=batch[\"input_path\"],\n            batch_output_path=batch[\"output_path\"],\n        )\n        if validation.get(\"approved_for_merge\"):\n            approved_batch_files.append(batch[\"output_path\"])\n        else:\n            failed_batch_ids.append(batch[\"batch_id\"])\n            errors.extend(validation.get(\"errors\", []))\n\n    if failed_batch_ids:\n        retry_decision = plan_retry(\n            step_name=\"scene_director\",\n            failure_type=\"screenplay_validation_failed\",\n            retry_count=0,\n            affected_batches=failed_batch_ids,\n            max_retries=max_retries,\n        )\n        errors.append(\n            {\n                \"code\": \"scene_director_lane_incomplete\",\n                \"message\": f\"Scene director lane still requires retry orchestration: {retry_decision}\",\n            }\n        )\n        return _lane_fail(errors, warnings)\n\n    screenplay_result = merge_screenplay_batches(\n        approved_batch_files,\n        output_path=paths[\"screenplay_path\"],\n    )\n    warnings.extend(screenplay_result.get(\"warnings\", []))\n    if not screenplay_result.get(\"ok\"):\n        return _lane_fail(screenplay_result.get(\"errors\", []), warnings)\n\n    screenplay = screenplay_result[\"screenplay\"]\n    validation = validate_screenplay(script_raw, screenplay.get(\"scenes\", []))\n    validation_path = Path(paths[\"screenplay_validation_path\"])\n    validation_path.write_text(json.dumps(validation, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    if not validation.get(\"valid\"):\n        retry_decision = plan_retry(\n            step_name=\"scene_director\",\n            failure_type=\"screenplay_validation_failed\",\n            retry_count=0,\n            affected_batches=[],\n            max_retries=max_retries,\n        )\n        errors.append(\n            {\n                \"code\": \"screenplay_validation_failed\",\n                \"message\": f\"Canonical screenplay failed validation and still needs supervisor retry control: {retry_decision}\",\n            }\n        )\n        return _lane_fail(errors, warnings)\n\n    write_checkpoint(\n        run_root,\n        \"b1_step1_screenplay\",\n        \"scene_director\",\n        [\"b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\"],\n        extra={\"scene_count\": screenplay_result.get(\"scene_count\", 0), \"model\": model},\n    )\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step1_screenplay.json\")\n\n    write_checkpoint(\n        run_root,\n        \"b1_step2_screenplay_validated\",\n        \"screenplay_validator\",\n        [\"b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json\"],\n        retries=0,\n        validation_passed=True,\n    )\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json\")\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"screenplay\": screenplay,\n        \"screenplay_result\": screenplay_result,\n        \"checkpoints_written\": checkpoints_written,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n        \"errors\": [],\n    }\n\n\ndef _run_tts_polish_lane(\n    *,\n    run_root: Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    channel_config: dict[str, Any],\n    paths: dict[str, Any],\n    screenplay: dict[str, Any],\n    model: str,\n    max_retries: int,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    warnings: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    errors: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    checkpoints_written: list[str] = []\n\n    batch_plan = plan_tts_polish_batches(screenplay)\n    warnings.extend(batch_plan.get(\"warnings\", []))\n    if not batch_plan.get(\"ok\"):\n        return _lane_fail(batch_plan.get(\"errors\", []), warnings)\n\n    prepared_batches = []\n    for batch in batch_plan.get(\"batches\", []):\n        batch_id = batch[\"batch_id\"]\n        input_path = Path(paths[\"tts_polish_inputs_root\"]) / f\"{batch_id}_input.json\"\n        output_path = Path(paths[\"tts_polish_intermediate_root\"]) / f\"{batch_id}_output.json\"\n        payload_result = write_tts_polish_payload(\n            run_root=run_root,\n            job=job,\n            screenplay=screenplay,\n            batch=batch,\n            channel_config=channel_config,\n            input_path=input_path,\n            output_path=output_path,\n        )\n        prepared_batches.append(\n            {\n                \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n                \"input_path\": payload_result[\"input_path\"],\n                \"output_path\": payload_result[\"output_path\"],\n                \"status\": \"queued\",\n            }\n        )\n\n    schedule = build_batch_schedule(\n        operator_name=\"tts_polish\",\n        batches=prepared_batches,\n        concurrency_cap=DEFAULT_TTS_POLISH_CONCURRENCY,\n    )\n    if not schedule.get(\"ok\"):\n        return _lane_fail(schedule.get(\"errors\", []), warnings)\n\n    execution_results = []\n    for wave in schedule.get(\"waves\", []):\n        for batch in wave.get(\"batches\", []):\n            execution_results.append(\n                _invoke_tts_polish_batch(\n                    input_path=batch[\"input_path\"],\n                    output_path=batch[\"output_path\"],\n                    model=model,\n                )\n            )\n\n    execution_summary = summarize_batch_execution(\n        operator_name=\"tts_polish\",\n        concurrency_cap=DEFAULT_TTS_POLISH_CONCURRENCY,\n        execution_results=execution_results,\n    )\n    warnings.extend(execution_summary.get(\"warnings\", []))\n\n    approved_batch_files: list[str] = []\n    failed_batch_ids: list[str] = []\n    for batch in prepared_batches:\n        validation = validate_tts_polish_output(\n            batch_payload_path=batch[\"input_path\"],\n            batch_output_path=batch[\"output_path\"],\n        )\n        if validation.get(\"approved_for_merge\"):\n            approved_batch_files.append(batch[\"output_path\"])\n        else:\n            failed_batch_ids.append(batch[\"batch_id\"])\n            errors.extend(validation.get(\"errors\", []))\n\n    if failed_batch_ids:\n        retry_decision = plan_retry(\n            step_name=\"tts_polish\",\n            failure_type=\"polish_validation_failed\",\n            retry_count=0,\n            affected_batches=failed_batch_ids,\n            max_retries=max_retries,\n        )\n        errors.append(\n            {\n                \"code\": \"tts_polish_lane_incomplete\",\n                \"message\": f\"TTS polish lane requires retry/reviewer orchestration for failed batches: {retry_decision}\",\n            }\n        )\n        return _lane_fail(errors, warnings)\n\n    polish_result = merge_tts_polish_batches(\n        approved_batch_files,\n        screenplay=screenplay,\n        output_path=paths[\"tts_polished_path\"],\n    )\n    warnings.extend(polish_result.get(\"warnings\", []))\n    if not polish_result.get(\"ok\"):\n        return _lane_fail(polish_result.get(\"errors\", []), warnings)\n\n    polished = polish_result[\"tts_polished\"]\n    validation = validate_polish(screenplay.get(\"scenes\", []), polished.get(\"scenes\", []))\n    validation_path = Path(paths[\"polish_validation_path\"])\n    validation_path.write_text(json.dumps(validation, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    if not validation.get(\"valid\"):\n        retry_decision = plan_retry(\n            step_name=\"tts_polish\",\n            failure_type=\"polish_validation_failed\",\n            retry_count=0,\n            affected_batches=[],\n            max_retries=max_retries,\n        )\n        errors.append(\n            {\n                \"code\": \"polish_validation_failed\",\n                \"message\": f\"Canonical TTS polish failed validation and still needs supervisor retry control: {retry_decision}\",\n            }\n        )\n        return _lane_fail(errors, warnings)\n\n    write_checkpoint(\n        run_root,\n        \"b1_step3_tts_polished\",\n        \"tts_polish\",\n        [\"b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\"],\n        extra={\"scene_count\": polish_result.get(\"scene_count\", 0), \"model\": model},\n    )\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step3_tts_polished.json\")\n\n    write_checkpoint(\n        run_root,\n        \"b1_step4_polish_validated\",\n        \"polish_validator\",\n        [\"b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json\"],\n        retries=0,\n        validation_passed=True,\n    )\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step4_polish_validated.json\")\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"tts_polished\": polished,\n        \"polish_result\": polish_result,\n        \"checkpoints_written\": checkpoints_written,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n        \"errors\": [],\n    }\n\n\ndef _run_scene_bible_lane(\n    *,\n    run_root: Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    screenplay: dict[str, Any],\n    polished: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    paths: dict[str, Any],\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    warnings: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    errors: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    checkpoints_written: list[str] = []\n\n    bible = build_scene_bible(polished, job, screenplay.get(\"scenes\", []))\n    schema_validation = validate_scene_bible_schema(bible)\n    warnings.extend(schema_validation.get(\"warnings\", []))\n    if not schema_validation.get(\"valid\"):\n        return _lane_fail(schema_validation.get(\"errors\", []), warnings)\n\n    scene_bible_path = write_scene_bible(bible, run_root)\n    write_checkpoint(\n        run_root,\n        \"b1_step5_scene_bible\",\n        \"scene_bible_builder\",\n        [\"scene_bible.json\"],\n        extra={\"scene_count\": len(bible.get(\"scenes\", []))},\n    )\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step5_scene_bible.json\")\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"scene_bible_path\": scene_bible_path,\n        \"scene_count\": len(bible.get(\"scenes\", [])),\n        \"checkpoints_written\": checkpoints_written,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n    }\n\n\ndef _invoke_scene_director_batch(*, input_path: str, output_path: str, model: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Transitional adapter hook for OpenClaw scene_director invocation.\n\n    Current behavior:\n    - attempts a narrow CLI-based compatibility invocation if `openclaw` is available\n    - fails explicitly otherwise\n    - never fabricates a successful operator result\n\n    Important:\n    - this is still a transitional adapter boundary\n    - the long-term goal is a cleaner runtime bridge to OpenClaw operators\n    \"\"\"\n    batch_id = Path(input_path).stem.replace(\"_input\", \"\")\n    openclaw_bin = shutil.which(\"openclaw\")\n    if not openclaw_bin:\n        return {\n            \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n            \"status\": \"failed\",\n            \"output_path\": output_path,\n            \"errors\": [\n                {\n                    \"code\": \"openclaw_cli_not_found\",\n                    \"message\": \"Cannot invoke scene_director: `openclaw` CLI not found in PATH.\",\n                }\n            ],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    command = [\n        openclaw_bin,\n        \"agent\",\n        \"--agent\",\n        \"op_s1_scene_director\",\n        \"--message\",\n        _build_scene_director_agent_message(input_path, output_path),\n        \"--json\",\n    ]\n    env = None\n\n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run(\n            command,\n            text=True,\n            capture_output=True,\n            check=False,\n            timeout=300,\n            env=env,\n        )\n    except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:\n        return {\n            \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n            \"status\": \"failed\",\n            \"output_path\": output_path,\n            \"errors\": [\n                {\n                    \"code\": \"operator_timeout\",\n                    \"message\": f\"scene_director invocation timed out for batch {batch_id}.\",\n                }\n            ],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n    except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n        return {\n            \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n            \"status\": \"failed\",\n            \"output_path\": output_path,\n            \"errors\": [\n                {\n                    \"code\": \"operator_invocation_failed\",\n                    \"message\": f\"scene_director invocation raised exception: {exc}\",\n                }\n            ],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    if result.returncode != 0:\n        return {\n            \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n            \"status\": \"failed\",\n            \"output_path\": output_path,\n            \"errors\": [\n                {\n                    \"code\": \"operator_nonzero_exit\",\n                    \"message\": (\n                        f\"scene_director CLI exited with code {result.returncode}: \"\n                        f\"{(result.stderr or result.stdout or '').strip()}\"\n                    ),\n                }\n            ],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    if not Path(output_path).exists():\n        stdout_text = (result.stdout or \"\").strip()\n        if stdout_text:\n            try:\n                parsed = json.loads(stdout_text)\n                Path(output_path).write_text(json.dumps(parsed, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n            except Exception:  # noqa: BLE001\n                pass\n\n    if not Path(output_path).exists():\n        return {\n            \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n            \"status\": \"failed\",\n            \"output_path\": output_path,\n            \"errors\": [\n                {\n                    \"code\": \"operator_no_output\",\n                    \"message\": \"scene_director invocation completed but no output artifact was produced.\",\n                }\n            ],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    return {\n        \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n        \"status\": \"completed\",\n        \"output_path\": output_path,\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n\n\ndef _invoke_tts_polish_batch(*, input_path: str, output_path: str, model: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Transitional adapter hook for OpenClaw TTS polish invocation.\"\"\"\n    batch_id = Path(input_path).stem.replace(\"_input\", \"\")\n    openclaw_bin = shutil.which(\"openclaw\")\n    if not openclaw_bin:\n        return {\n            \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n            \"status\": \"failed\",\n            \"output_path\": output_path,\n            \"errors\": [\n                {\n                    \"code\": \"openclaw_cli_not_found\",\n                    \"message\": \"Cannot invoke tts_polish: `openclaw` CLI not found in PATH.\",\n                }\n            ],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    command = [\n        openclaw_bin,\n        \"agent\",\n        \"--agent\",\n        \"op_s1_tts_polish\",\n        \"--message\",\n        _build_tts_polish_agent_message(input_path, output_path),\n        \"--json\",\n    ]\n    env = None\n\n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run(\n            command,\n            text=True,\n            capture_output=True,\n            check=False,\n            timeout=300,\n            env=env,\n        )\n    except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:\n        return {\n            \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n            \"status\": \"failed\",\n            \"output_path\": output_path,\n            \"errors\": [\n                {\n                    \"code\": \"operator_timeout\",\n                    \"message\": f\"tts_polish invocation timed out for batch {batch_id}.\",\n                }\n            ],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n    except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n        return {\n            \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n            \"status\": \"failed\",\n            \"output_path\": output_path,\n            \"errors\": [\n                {\n                    \"code\": \"operator_invocation_failed\",\n                    \"message\": f\"tts_polish invocation raised exception: {exc}\",\n                }\n            ],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    if result.returncode != 0:\n        return {\n            \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n            \"status\": \"failed\",\n            \"output_path\": output_path,\n            \"errors\": [\n                {\n                    \"code\": \"operator_nonzero_exit\",\n                    \"message\": (\n                        f\"tts_polish CLI exited with code {result.returncode}: \"\n                        f\"{(result.stderr or result.stdout or '').strip()}\"\n                    ),\n                }\n            ],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    if not Path(output_path).exists():\n        stdout_text = (result.stdout or \"\").strip()\n        if stdout_text:\n            try:\n                parsed = json.loads(stdout_text)\n                Path(output_path).write_text(json.dumps(parsed, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n            except Exception:  # noqa: BLE001\n                pass\n\n    if not Path(output_path).exists():\n        return {\n            \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n            \"status\": \"failed\",\n            \"output_path\": output_path,\n            \"errors\": [\n                {\n                    \"code\": \"operator_no_output\",\n                    \"message\": \"tts_polish invocation completed but no output artifact was produced.\",\n                }\n            ],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    return {\n        \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n        \"status\": \"completed\",\n        \"output_path\": output_path,\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n\n\ndef _build_scene_director_agent_message(input_path: str, output_path: str) -> str:\n    return (\n        \"You are executing one canonical S1 scene_director batch. \"\n        f\"Read the batch payload JSON at: {input_path}. \"\n        \"Follow the op_s1_scene_director workspace contract exactly. \"\n        \"Write only the final batch result JSON to the output_path declared in the payload. \"\n        f\"Expected output artifact path: {output_path}. \"\n        \"Do not do visual planning, TTS polish, merge logic, or supervisor logic. \"\n        \"Critical rule: output spans must be batch-relative, never global. \"\n        \"The payload field batch.start_word is global metadata only and must NEVER be used as the output offset. \"\n        \"If the payload says batch.start_word=718 and word_count=749, your output spans must still run locally from 1 to 749. \"\n        \"Before writing the JSON, verify that every scene start_word/end_word is inside the local batch range 1..batch.word_count. \"\n        \"Also verify that narration_original matches exactly the source text covered by each declared span. \"\n        \"If any scene uses global coordinates or span/text mismatch, the batch is invalid and must be regenerated before writing. \"\n        \"If the payload is invalid or impossible, fail clearly instead of improvising.\"\n    )\n\n\ndef _build_tts_polish_agent_message(input_path: str, output_path: str) -> str:\n    return (\n        \"You are executing one canonical S1 tts_polish batch. \"\n        f\"Read the batch payload JSON at: {input_path}. \"\n        \"Follow the op_s1_tts_polish workspace contract exactly. \"\n        \"Write only the final batch result JSON to the output_path declared in the payload. \"\n        f\"Expected output artifact path: {output_path}. \"\n        \"Do not do scene restructuring, merge logic, validation ownership, or supervisor logic. \"\n        \"If the payload is invalid or impossible, fail clearly instead of improvising.\"\n    )\n\n\ndef _load_config(account: str, language: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    candidate_paths = [\n        ACCOUNTS_DIR / str(account) / f\"{language}.yaml\",\n        Path(__file__).resolve().parents[2] / \"accounts\" / str(account) / f\"{language}.yaml\",\n    ]\n    for config_path in candidate_paths:\n        if config_path.exists():\n            with open(config_path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n                return yaml.safe_load(f) or {}\n    raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Channel config not found: {candidate_paths[0]}\")\n\n\ndef _lane_fail(errors: list[dict[str, Any]], warnings: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    return {\n        \"ok\": False,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n\n\ndef _failed_result(\n    run_root: Path,\n    errors: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    warnings: list[dict[str, Any]],\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    return summarize_s1_result(\n        run_root=run_root,\n        screenplay_result={},\n        polish_result={},\n        scene_bible_path=None,\n        checkpoints_written=[],\n        warnings=warnings,\n        errors=errors,\n    )\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775060391071}}
{"type":"message","id":"2854962c","parentId":"8bd52ff9","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:19:51.099Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01N4uBm9BMhnamHiLMTsjQMm","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"Scene Director Runner — LEGACY compatibility wrapper around the newer S1 batch flow.\n\nLEGACY STATUS:\n- This module remains only because the prototype entrypoint `runtime.s1.s1_start`\n  still imports `run_scene_director` / `save_screenplay` and legacy tests still depend on it.\n- It does NOT represent the canonical OpenClaw runtime architecture for S1.\n\nCanonical architecture now expects:\n- supervisor-owned batch planning\n- explicit IO adapter bridge\n- OpenClaw `scene_director` operator execution\n- per-batch validation\n- deterministic merge into canonical screenplay.json\n\nThis wrapper keeps older call sites functional while adapting them to a newer\nscene object shape expected by the supervisor skills/contracts.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\nfrom openai import OpenAI\n\n\n# Max words per chunk sent to the model\nCHUNK_TARGET_WORDS = 600\n\n\ndef run_scene_director(\n    script_raw: str,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    config: dict[str, Any],\n    model: str = \"gpt-4.1-mini\",\n) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n    \"\"\"Split raw script into structured scenes using the newer scene contract.\n\n    Compatibility behavior:\n    - still accepts the old prototype signature used by `s1_start.py`\n    - still chunks long scripts internally\n    - but now returns scene objects aligned with the newer S1 contracts\n    \"\"\"\n    words_min, words_max = config.get(\"scene_words_range\", [35, 75])\n\n    chunks = _split_into_chunks(script_raw, CHUNK_TARGET_WORDS)\n\n    client = OpenAI()\n    all_scenes: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    global_scene_counter = 0\n    global_word_cursor = 1\n\n    for chunk_text in chunks:\n        chunk_word_count = len(_normalize_text(chunk_text).split())\n        system_prompt = f\"\"\"You are the scene_director for S1 pre-production.\n\nYour job is to transform this script batch into an editorially intentional sequence of scenes.\n\nCRITICAL RULES:\n1. Use clean narrative scene boundaries. Do NOT cut mid-sentence unless absolutely necessary.\n2. Preserve EVERY SINGLE WORD of the input text in narration_original. Do NOT add, remove, summarize, paraphrase, or modify wording.\n3. The concatenation of all narration_original fields must reproduce the input text EXACTLY, word for word.\n4. Use batch-relative word coordinates. The first word in this batch is word 1.\n5. Do not generate global scene IDs.\n6. Do not do visual planning, prompt writing, asset planning, or TTS polish.\n7. For each scene, return:\n   - scene_local_id: sequential within the batch (scene_01, scene_02, ...)\n   - scene_title: short clear label\n   - scene_summary: concise summary of the scene's purpose/content\n   - narrative_function: the narrative role of the scene\n   - narration_original: exact source text for that scene\n   - start_word: batch-relative start word\n   - end_word: batch-relative end word\n   - estimated_scene_word_count: exact word count implied by the span\n8. No gaps and no overlaps between scene spans.\n9. Aim for scene sizes compatible with configured scene_words_range ({words_min}-{words_max}) when natural narrative structure allows.\n\nOUTPUT: Return JSON object with a 'scenes' array. Nothing else.\"\"\"\n\n        response = client.chat.completions.create(\n            model=model,\n            messages=[\n                {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": system_prompt},\n                {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": f\"Transform this text batch into ordered scenes:\\n\\n{chunk_text}\"},\n            ],\n            temperature=0.1,\n            response_format={\"type\": \"json_object\"},\n        )\n\n        content = response.choices[0].message.content\n        parsed = json.loads(content)\n        chunk_scenes = _extract_scenes(parsed)\n        _normalize_chunk_scenes(chunk_scenes, chunk_text)\n\n        for scene in chunk_scenes:\n            global_scene_counter += 1\n            scene[\"scene_id\"] = f\"scene_{global_scene_counter:03d}\"\n            scene[\"source_batch_id\"] = None\n            scene[\"source_batch_scene_index\"] = None\n            scene[\"source_scene_local_id\"] = scene.get(\"scene_local_id\")\n            scene[\"global_start_word\"] = global_word_cursor + int(scene[\"start_word\"]) - 1\n            scene[\"global_end_word\"] = global_word_cursor + int(scene[\"end_word\"]) - 1\n\n        all_scenes.extend(chunk_scenes)\n        global_word_cursor += chunk_word_count\n\n    return all_scenes\n\n\ndef _split_into_chunks(text: str, target_words: int) -> list[str]:\n    \"\"\"Split text into chunks at sentence boundaries.\"\"\"\n    sentences = re.split(r\"(?<=[.!?])\\s+\", text.strip())\n    chunks = []\n    current_chunk = []\n    current_words = 0\n\n    for sentence in sentences:\n        word_count = len(sentence.split())\n        if current_words + word_count > target_words and current_chunk:\n            chunks.append(\" \".join(current_chunk))\n            current_chunk = [sentence]\n            current_words = word_count\n        else:\n            current_chunk.append(sentence)\n            current_words += word_count\n\n    if current_chunk:\n        chunks.append(\" \".join(current_chunk))\n\n    return chunks\n\n\ndef _extract_scenes(parsed: Any) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n    \"\"\"Extract scenes list from various model response formats.\"\"\"\n    if isinstance(parsed, dict):\n        if \"scenes\" in parsed:\n            scenes = parsed[\"scenes\"]\n            if isinstance(scenes, list):\n                return scenes\n        for val in parsed.values():\n            if isinstance(val, list) and len(val) > 0:\n                return val\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unexpected response: dict with keys {list(parsed.keys())}\")\n    if isinstance(parsed, list):\n        return parsed\n    raise ValueError(f\"Unexpected response format: {type(parsed)}\")\n\n\ndef _normalize_chunk_scenes(scenes: list[dict[str, Any]], chunk_text: str) -> None:\n    chunk_tokens = _normalize_text(chunk_text).split()\n    cursor = 1\n\n    for index, scene in enumerate(scenes, start=1):\n        if not isinstance(scene, dict):\n            raise ValueError(f\"Scene {index} is not an object\")\n\n        scene_local_id = scene.get(\"scene_local_id\")\n        if not isinstance(scene_local_id, str) or not scene_local_id.strip():\n            scene_local_id = f\"scene_{index:02d}\"\n        scene[\"scene_local_id\"] = scene_local_id\n\n        narration_original = scene.get(\"narration_original\")\n        if not isinstance(narration_original, str) or not narration_original.strip():\n            raise ValueError(f\"Scene {scene_local_id} has no narration_original\")\n\n        narration_tokens = _normalize_text(narration_original).split()\n        word_count = len(narration_tokens)\n        if word_count == 0:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Scene {scene_local_id} has empty narration_original\")\n\n        expected_tokens = chunk_tokens[cursor - 1: cursor - 1 + word_count]\n        if narration_tokens != expected_tokens:\n            raise ValueError(\n                f\"Scene {scene_local_id} narration_original does not match chunk source at words {cursor}-{cursor + word_count - 1}\"\n            )\n\n        scene.setdefault(\"scene_title\", f\"Scene {index}\")\n        scene.setdefault(\"scene_summary\", scene[\"scene_title\"])\n        scene.setdefault(\"narrative_function\", \"narrative progression\")\n        scene[\"start_word\"] = cursor\n        scene[\"end_word\"] = cursor + word_count - 1\n        scene[\"estimated_scene_word_count\"] = word_count\n\n        cursor += word_count\n\n    if cursor - 1 != len(chunk_tokens):\n        raise ValueError(\n            f\"Chunk scene coverage incomplete: covered {cursor - 1} of {len(chunk_tokens)} words\"\n        )\n\n\ndef _normalize_text(text: str) -> str:\n    text = text.replace(\"\\r\\n\", \" \").replace(\"\\n\", \" \").replace(\"\\t\", \" \")\n    return re.sub(r\"\\s+\", \" \", text).strip()\n\n\ndef save_screenplay(\n    scenes: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    video_root: Path,\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Save screenplay.json to b1_pre_production/.\"\"\"\n    output_dir = Path(video_root) / \"b1_pre_production\"\n    output_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    path = output_dir / \"screenplay.json\"\n    screenplay = {\n        \"scene_count\": len(scenes),\n        \"scenes\": scenes,\n    }\n    path.write_text(\n        json.dumps(screenplay, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False),\n        encoding=\"utf-8\",\n    )\n    return str(path)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775060391085}}
{"type":"message","id":"25742c1c","parentId":"2854962c","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:19:57.891Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to look at the scene_director_io_adapter to understand the batch payload, particularly `batch.start_word`, and the script_batch_planner to understand how batches are structured.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_017xAtdrPL2Y11zRM8tsyKMz","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\scene_director_io_adapter.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_019Fqo1i1mSikqhXRsVtnD2y","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\script_batch_planner.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":219,"cacheRead":16757,"cacheWrite":10738,"totalTokens":27715,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.003285,"cacheRead":0.0050271,"cacheWrite":0.0402675,"total":0.0485826}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775060391099,"responseId":"msg_01NBcwvpwNJvfzQJM6P5ZUGt"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5e5ec460","parentId":"25742c1c","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:19:58.304Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_017xAtdrPL2Y11zRM8tsyKMz","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef build_scene_director_payload(\n    *,\n    run_root: str | Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    batch: dict[str, Any],\n    channel_config: dict[str, Any],\n    output_path: str | Path,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    run_root = Path(run_root)\n    output_path = Path(output_path)\n\n    account = job.get(\"account\")\n    language = job.get(\"language\")\n    job_id = job.get(\"job_id\")\n\n    payload = {\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n        \"account\": account,\n        \"language\": language,\n        \"run_root\": str(run_root),\n        \"batch\": {\n            \"batch_id\": batch.get(\"batch_id\"),\n            \"start_word\": batch.get(\"start_word\"),\n            \"end_word\": batch.get(\"end_word\"),\n            \"word_count\": batch.get(\"word_count\"),\n            \"text\": batch.get(\"text\"),\n        },\n        \"scene_words_range\": channel_config.get(\"scene_words_range\"),\n        \"style_context\": {\n            \"channel_name\": job.get(\"channel_name\"),\n            \"reason\": job.get(\"reason\"),\n        },\n        \"instructions\": {\n            \"task\": \"Transform this script batch into an editorially intentional sequence of scenes for screenplay generation.\",\n            \"requirements\": [\n                \"Preserve narrative meaning and order.\",\n                \"Return scene objects only for this batch.\",\n                \"Each scene must include scene_local_id, scene_title, scene_summary, narrative_function, narration_original, start_word, end_word, estimated_scene_word_count.\",\n                \"Use batch-relative word coordinates: the first word in this batch is word 1.\",\n                \"scene_local_id must be sequential within the batch (scene_01, scene_02, ...).\",\n                \"Do not generate global scene IDs.\",\n                \"Do not rewrite the story beyond what is needed for clean scene segmentation.\",\n                \"Do not do visual planning, asset planning, prompt writing, or shot design in this step.\",\n                \"Do not polish for TTS in this step.\",\n                \"Do not leave gaps or overlaps between scene text spans.\",\n                \"narration_original must match the original source text assigned to each scene.\",\n            ],\n        },\n        \"output_path\": str(output_path),\n    }\n\n    return payload\n\n\ndef write_scene_director_payload(\n    *,\n    run_root: str | Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    batch: dict[str, Any],\n    channel_config: dict[str, Any],\n    input_path: str | Path,\n    output_path: str | Path,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    input_path = Path(input_path)\n    output_path = Path(output_path)\n    input_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    payload = build_scene_director_payload(\n        run_root=run_root,\n        job=job,\n        batch=batch,\n        channel_config=channel_config,\n        output_path=output_path,\n    )\n\n    input_path.write_text(json.dumps(payload, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"input_path\": str(input_path),\n        \"output_path\": str(output_path),\n        \"batch_id\": batch.get(\"batch_id\"),\n        \"payload\": payload,\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775060398288}}
{"type":"message","id":"10733ab1","parentId":"5e5ec460","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:19:58.318Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_019Fqo1i1mSikqhXRsVtnD2y","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef plan_script_batches(\n    script_text: str,\n    *,\n    target_words_per_batch: int = 750,\n    min_words_per_batch: int = 450,\n    max_words_per_batch: int = 950,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n\n    if not script_text or not script_text.strip():\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"batch_count\": 0,\n            \"batches\": [],\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"empty_script\", \"message\": \"Cannot plan batches for empty script text\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    normalized_text = script_text.strip()\n    total_words = len(normalized_text.split())\n\n    paragraphs = [p.strip() for p in re.split(r\"\\n\\s*\\n+\", normalized_text) if p.strip()]\n    if not paragraphs:\n        paragraphs = [normalized_text]\n\n    batches: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    current_parts: list[str] = []\n    current_word_count = 0\n    running_word_index = 1\n    batch_number = 1\n\n    def flush_batch() -> None:\n        nonlocal current_parts, current_word_count, running_word_index, batch_number\n        if not current_parts:\n            return\n        batch_text = \"\\n\\n\".join(current_parts).strip()\n        batch_words = len(batch_text.split())\n        start_word = running_word_index\n        end_word = running_word_index + batch_words - 1\n        batches.append(\n            {\n                \"batch_id\": f\"sd_{batch_number:03d}\",\n                \"start_word\": start_word,\n                \"end_word\": end_word,\n                \"word_count\": batch_words,\n                \"text\": batch_text,\n            }\n        )\n        running_word_index = end_word + 1\n        batch_number += 1\n        current_parts = []\n        current_word_count = 0\n\n    for paragraph in paragraphs:\n        paragraph_words = len(paragraph.split())\n\n        # Oversized single paragraph: split by sentences as fallback\n        if paragraph_words > max_words_per_batch:\n            if current_parts:\n                flush_batch()\n            sentence_chunks = _split_paragraph_to_sentence_chunks(\n                paragraph,\n                target_words_per_batch=target_words_per_batch,\n                max_words_per_batch=max_words_per_batch,\n            )\n            for chunk in sentence_chunks:\n                current_parts = [chunk]\n                current_word_count = len(chunk.split())\n                flush_batch()\n            continue\n\n        if current_word_count == 0:\n            current_parts.append(paragraph)\n            current_word_count = paragraph_words\n            continue\n\n        if current_word_count + paragraph_words <= target_words_per_batch:\n            current_parts.append(paragraph)\n            current_word_count += paragraph_words\n            continue\n\n        if current_word_count < min_words_per_batch and current_word_count + paragraph_words <= max_words_per_batch:\n            current_parts.append(paragraph)\n            current_word_count += paragraph_words\n            continue\n\n        flush_batch()\n        current_parts.append(paragraph)\n        current_word_count = paragraph_words\n\n    if current_parts:\n        flush_batch()\n\n    if not batches:\n        errors.append({\"code\": \"no_batches_generated\", \"message\": \"Batch planner failed to produce any batches\"})\n\n    if batches and len(batches[-1][\"text\"].split()) < min_words_per_batch and len(batches) > 1:\n        warnings.append(\n            {\n                \"code\": \"small_final_batch\",\n                \"message\": f\"Final batch is smaller than recommended ({batches[-1]['word_count']} words)\",\n            }\n        )\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": len(errors) == 0,\n        \"total_words\": total_words,\n        \"batch_count\": len(batches),\n        \"target_words_per_batch\": target_words_per_batch,\n        \"min_words_per_batch\": min_words_per_batch,\n        \"max_words_per_batch\": max_words_per_batch,\n        \"batches\": batches,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n\n\ndef plan_script_batches_from_file(\n    script_path: str | Path,\n    *,\n    target_words_per_batch: int = 750,\n    min_words_per_batch: int = 450,\n    max_words_per_batch: int = 950,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    script_path = Path(script_path)\n    if not script_path.exists():\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"batch_count\": 0,\n            \"batches\": [],\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"missing_script_file\", \"message\": f\"Script file not found: {script_path}\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    text = script_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    result = plan_script_batches(\n        text,\n        target_words_per_batch=target_words_per_batch,\n        min_words_per_batch=min_words_per_batch,\n        max_words_per_batch=max_words_per_batch,\n    )\n    result[\"script_path\"] = str(script_path)\n    return result\n\n\ndef _split_paragraph_to_sentence_chunks(\n    paragraph: str,\n    *,\n    target_words_per_batch: int,\n    max_words_per_batch: int,\n) -> list[str]:\n    sentences = [s.strip() for s in re.split(r\"(?<=[.!?])\\s+\", paragraph) if s.strip()]\n    if not sentences:\n        return [paragraph]\n\n    chunks: list[str] = []\n    current: list[str] = []\n    current_words = 0\n\n    for sentence in sentences:\n        sentence_words = len(sentence.split())\n\n        if current_words == 0:\n            current.append(sentence)\n            current_words = sentence_words\n            continue\n\n        if current_words + sentence_words <= target_words_per_batch:\n            current.append(sentence)\n            current_words += sentence_words\n            continue\n\n        if current_words + sentence_words <= max_words_per_batch:\n            current.append(sentence)\n            current_words += sentence_words\n            continue\n\n        chunks.append(\" \".join(current).strip())\n        current = [sentence]\n        current_words = sentence_words\n\n    if current:\n        chunks.append(\" \".join(current).strip())\n\n    return chunks\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775060398305}}
{"type":"message","id":"a88a44f9","parentId":"10733ab1","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:20:13.342Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have enough information. Let me analyze the root cause of the bug.\n\nThe key issue is in `_invoke_scene_director_batch` in `supervisor_runtime.py`. The command:\n\n```python\ncommand = [\n    openclaw_bin,\n    \"agent\",\n    \"--agent\",\n    \"op_s1_scene_director\",\n    \"--message\",\n    _build_scene_director_agent_message(input_path, output_path),\n    \"--json\",\n]\n```\n\nThe message sent to the agent includes explicit instructions about batch-relative coordinates, but the core issue is **session/context reuse**.\n\n\nWhen `openclaw agent` is called multiple times for the same agent, OpenClaw reuses the session by default, so each batch invocation carries over context from previous batches. The agent remembers global word positions from earlier batches and starts outputting global indices instead of batch-relative ones, causing the contamination.\n\nThe solution is to use a flag like `--local` to force a fresh session for each invocation. I need to verify what CLI options OpenClaw actually supports for this isolation.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01SoWqedfZNrvadX9EARwkS9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw agent --help 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":473,"cacheRead":27495,"cacheWrite":2890,"totalTokens":30859,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.007095000000000001,"cacheRead":0.008248499999999999,"cacheWrite":0.0108375,"total":0.026184}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775060398318,"responseId":"msg_01Gcxn9Avd6tKyBEtkd9QjKT"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4576a9b1","parentId":"a88a44f9","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:20:17.939Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01SoWqedfZNrvadX9EARwkS9","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.28 (f9b1079) — Your AI assistant, now without the $3,499 headset.\n\nUsage: openclaw agent [options]\n\nRun an agent turn via the Gateway (use --local for embedded)\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>               Agent id (overrides routing bindings)\n  --channel <channel>        Delivery channel:\n                             last|telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|line\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n                             | xhigh\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":4542,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.28 (f9b1079) — Your AI assistant, now without the $3,499 headset.\n\nUsage: openclaw agent [options]\n\nRun an agent turn via the Gateway (use --local for embedded)\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>               Agent id (overrides routing bindings)\n  --channel <channel>        Delivery channel:\n                             last|telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|line\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n                             | xhigh\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent","cwd":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775060417917}}
{"type":"message","id":"2972d773","parentId":"4576a9b1","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:20:46.479Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the key information. Let me analyze:\n\n1. `openclaw agent --agent ... --json` - without `--local`, this runs via the Gateway\n2. Without `--local`, calls go through the Gateway, which **routes to a session** based on agent id\n3. The Gateway likely maintains/reuses sessions for the same agent id across calls\n4. This means batch 1, 2, 3... are ALL running in the **same persistent session** with accumulated context/history\n\nThe bug: the agent in session accumulates context from previous batches. When batch 2 is processed, the model has seen batch 1's output in its conversation history, and may use global coordinates (e.g., if batch 1 ended at word 749, batch 2's model thinks its first word is 750 instead of 1).\n \nSo the issue is that `_invoke_scene_director_batch` and `_invoke_tts_polish_batch` in `supervisor_runtime.py` don't use the `--local` flag, which means each batch call reuses the same Gateway session and accumulates conversation history. The fix is to add `--local` to both commands so each batch runs in isolation without carrying over context from previous batches.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"## Findings\n\n### Root Cause: Confirmed — Gateway Session Reuse\n\nThe `openclaw agent --help` output reveals the critical distinction:\n\n> **Without `--local`**: runs via the Gateway — which maintains/reuses a persistent session\n> **`--local`**: runs the embedded agent locally, isolated (requires API keys in shell)\n\nIn `supervisor_runtime.py`, `_invoke_scene_director_batch` builds this command:\n```python\ncommand = [\n    openclaw_bin, \"agent\",\n    \"--agent\", \"op_s1_scene_director\",\n    \"--message\", ...,\n    \"--json\",\n]\n# NO --local flag\n```\n\nWithout `--local`, every batch call to `op_s1_scene_director` goes through the Gateway and **lands in the same persistent session** for that agent. The session accumulates conversation history: batch 1's exchange (including its output with scenes at words 1-749) stays in context when batch 2 is called. The model sees prior outputs and \"remembers\" that last batch ended at word 749 — so batch 2 continues from 750 instead of resetting to local word 1. This perfectly explains why batches 2-5 output global indices.\n\n### Is `--local` the Right Fix?\n\n**Yes, with a caveat.** `--local` forces each invocation to run as a fresh embedded agent with no session persistence — exactly the clean per-call isolation needed. Each batch gets a blank slate.\n\nThe caveat: `--local` **requires model provider API keys in the shell environment**. The current code passes `env=None` (inherits process environment), so this should work as-is if keys are set. No env injection change is needed unless keys are missing.\n\n### Actionable Fix for `supervisor_runtime.py`\n\n**In `_invoke_scene_director_batch`**, add `\"--local\"` to the command:\n\n```python\ncommand = [\n    openclaw_bin,\n    \"agent\",\n    \"--local\",                    # ← ADD THIS\n    \"--agent\",\n    \"op_s1_scene_director\",\n    \"--message\",\n    _build_scene_director_agent_message(input_path, output_path),\n    \"--json\",\n]\n```\n\n**Same fix in `_invoke_tts_polish_batch`** — same pattern, same risk (though TTS polish may be less affected since it doesn't deal with word coordinates).\n\n### Why the Agent Message Warning Alone Is Insufficient\n\nThe current agent message already contains an explicit warning:\n> *\"The payload field batch.start_word is global metadata only and must NEVER be used as the output offset.\"*\n\nBut this doesn't help when the model's **conversation history from prior batches** shows local coords starting at 1, then 750, then 1500. The model pattern-matches against its own prior turn outputs, overriding the instruction. Session isolation eliminates this entirely.\n\n### Summary\n\n| | Without `--local` | With `--local` |\n|---|---|---|\n| Session | Persistent, shared across batches | Fresh per invocation |\n| Prior batch history visible | ✅ Yes → causes global offset drift | ❌ No → clean isolation |\n| Correct for batch operators | ❌ | ✅ |\n\n**One-line fix**: add `\"--local\"` to both `_invoke_scene_director_batch` and `_invoke_tts_polish_batch` command arrays in `supervisor_runtime.py`."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":1137,"cacheRead":30385,"cacheWrite":679,"totalTokens":32202,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.017055,"cacheRead":0.0091155,"cacheWrite":0.00254625,"total":0.028719750000000002}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775060417940,"responseId":"msg_01PogkmWPFtTsbZ8XWUEzi8e"}}
